data.text:
Sunday, May 19, 2024 • 1:00–4:00pm.:

Now in its 31st year, the original "Party in the Park" has become one of the Midwest's finest food and wine celebrations.

Over 400 wines from all over the world will be available to sample; Live music will be provided by the Kim Kelly Orchestra, the Belgian Beer Garden will return; and various local eateries are slated for this year's event.

A silent auction will also be available with fabulous prizes from Dayton area businesses, as well as live painting from local artist, Bley Hack.

All proceeds benefit Dayton History's mission to inspire generations by connecting them with the unique people, places, and events that changed Dayton and the world.

Where: Carillon Historical Park behind Carillon Brewing Co. Rain or shine.

When: Sunday, May 19, 2024 • 1:00–4:00pm.

Tickets*: $80 in advance, $85 day-of. Purchase in-person at all Arrow Wine locations, Carillon Historical Park, or online.

*Must be 21 to attend.

https://www.daytonhistory.org/events/special-events/fleurs-de-fete/

About Carillon Historical Park

Carillon Historical Park is part of Dayton History, a private non-profit organization established to preserve, share, and celebrate our region’s unique history. The Park's 65-acre campus is home to over 30 historic structures and cares for over three million artifacts. In addition to Carillon Historical Park, Dayton History owns and operates the Carillon Brewing Co., Culp's Café, Hawthorn Hill, the Patterson Homestead, the Mound Cold War Discovery Center, and the Dayton History Archive Center.

Dayton History • 1000 Carillon Blvd. • Dayton, OH 45409https://www.daytonhistory.org
